text: mostly because it makes me giggle
Heh, that's pretty cute, especially with Purphoros type stuff.
it's also a card taht confuses people
Well, the words printed on it being wrong doesn't help with that.
And its reserved list, so that won't ever get fixed. = /
the words aren't wrong
the problem is that people read "first" and assume it only works on the first creature
but it's referencing the creature that died
I think the confusing part is that the first half of the card references a creature going into any graveyard and any person has a creature in play, then it gets specific about your yard.
yeah, it's just poorly worded
just not wrong

Reading the rules information it did have an errata so the "your graveyard
" is no longer correct,  which might be Dougs point.

On first read-through, people think that it only works for you, and isn't universal, because of the "your graveyard" portion of things.

Then, once they figure that part out, they get to go look up an intervening if clause in the rulebook and try to understand that. Rules-wise, it's a very confusing card.
Fun as hell, though, especially with [[Massacre Girl]].
